Date:  0/0/1980
Source:  Tussock Ranges
Author:  McLEOD
Vol / Page:  203
Edition:
Quote:  The reward was to get your name on the silver replica of a mustering billy, the old-fashioned wide-bottomed pot with a mug which fitted inside to form a lid, and was boiled, when time permitted, hanging from the end of a mustering stick over a hastily-lit fire.
